The annotation is inserted directly after a chunk's [[@defn]] line,
so it precedes every [[@text]] line of the chunk and a streaming
consumer knows the language before it sees any code.  The grammar
allows at most one [[@language]] per [[@begin code]]/[[@end code]]
pair, so a chunk that is already annotated---for instance because
[[autolang]] ran twice---is left alone; [[chunk_languages]] has
already treated the existing annotation as authoritative, making a
second run a no-op rather than an error.

